<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<sec id="s5" class="sec">
 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Statistical Analyses</div>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Probit analysis conducted using SAS 9.4 statistical package was used to calculate LC
  <sub>50</sub> and LC
  <sub>95</sub> values for different oil treatments. To examine the effect of oil mixtures, we used cotoxicity coefficient (CTC) to determine whether the interaction was additive, synergistic or additive (
  <a rid="CIT0043" ref-type="bibr" href="#CIT0043">Sun and Johnson 1960</a>). This was computed as follows with garlic serving as the standard:
 </p>
 <div class="disp-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <div id="m1" class="math">
   <div class="mrow">
    <span class="mtext">Toxicity index </span>
    <div class="mrow">
     <span class="mo">(</span>
     <div class="mrow">
      <span class="mtext">TI</span>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">)</span>
    </div>
    <span class="mtext"> of garlic </span>
    <div class="mrow">
     <span class="mo">(</span>
     <span class="mtext">G</span>
     <span class="mo">)</span>
    </div>
    <span class="mo">=</span>
    <span class="mtext">100</span>
    <span class="mn">,</span>
   </div>
  </div>
 </div>
 <div class="disp-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <div id="m2" class="math">
   <div class="mrow">
    <span class="mtext">TI of asafoetida </span>
    <div class="mrow">
     <span class="mo">(</span>
     <span class="mtext">A</span>
     <span class="mo">)</span>
    </div>
    <span class="mtext">=</span>
    <div class="mfrac">
     <div class="mrow">
      <div class="msub">
       <div class="mrow">
        <span class="mtext">LC</span>
       </div>
       <div class="mrow">
        <span class="mtext">50</span>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span class="mtext"> of G</span>
     </div>
     <div class="mrow">
      <div class="msub">
       <div class="mrow">
        <span class="mtext">LC</span>
       </div>
       <div class="mrow">
        <span class="mtext">50</span>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span class="mtext"> of A</span>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span class="mo">×</span>
    <span class="mtext">100</span>
   </div>
  </div>
 </div>
 <div class="disp-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <div id="m3" class="math">
   <div class="mrow">
    <span class="mtext">Actual TI of mixture </span>
    <div class="mrow">
     <span class="mo">(</span>
     <div class="mrow">
      <span class="mtext">AG</span>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">)</span>
    </div>
    <span class="mtext">=</span>
    <div class="mfrac">
     <div class="mrow">
      <div class="msub">
       <div class="mrow">
        <span class="mtext">LC</span>
       </div>
       <div class="mrow">
        <span class="mtext">50</span>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span class="mtext"> of G</span>
     </div>
     <div class="mrow">
      <div class="msub">
       <div class="mrow">
        <span class="mtext">LC</span>
       </div>
       <div class="mrow">
        <span class="mtext">50</span>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span class="mtext"> of AG</span>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span class="mi"/>
    <span class="mo">×</span>
    <span class="mtext">100</span>
   </div>
  </div>
 </div>
 <div class="disp-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <div id="m4" class="math">
   <div class="mrow">
    <span class="mtext">Theoretical TI of AG = TI of G </span>
    <span class="mo">×</span>
    <span class="mtext"> % of G in AG + TI of A </span>
    <span class="mo">×</span>
    <span class="mtext"> % of A in AG</span>
   </div>
  </div>
 </div>
 <div class="disp-formula" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <div id="m5" class="math">
   <div class="mrow">
    <span class="mtext">CTC = </span>
    <div class="mfrac">
     <div class="mrow">
      <span class="mtext">Actual TI of AG</span>
     </div>
     <div class="mrow">
      <span class="mtext">Theoretical TI of AG</span>
     </div>
    </div>
    <span class="mi"/>
    <span class="mo">×</span>
    <span class="mtext">100</span>
   </div>
  </div>
 </div>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">A CTC of a mixture near 100 indicates probability of additive effects while CTC value lower than or greater than 100 indicates antagonism and synergism, respectively (
  <a rid="CIT0043" ref-type="bibr" href="#CIT0043">Sun and Johnson 1960</a>, 
  <a rid="CIT0023" ref-type="bibr" href="#CIT0023">Islam et al. 2010</a>).
 </p>
</sec>
